inations: Journal of Medieval Art and Architecture |volume=6 |issue=1 |year=2017 |pages=5\u201337}} {{open access}}\n*[[Jennifer Baird|Baird, J. A.]]\u00a0 and C. Taylor, eds. 2011, ''Ancient Graffiti in Context''. New York: Routledge.\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{wiktionary|graffiti}}\n{{commons|Graffiti}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{Cite NIE|wstitle=Graffiti|year=1905 |short=x}}\n\n{{Street Art}}\n{{hiphop}}\n{{Media culture}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Graffiti and unauthorised signage| ]]\n[[Category:Visual arts genres]]\n[[Category:Painting techniques]]\n[[Category:Street culture]]\n[[Category:Writing]]\n[[Category:Organized crime activity]]\n", "name_user": "Matthew T Rader", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added a couple images of graffiti from Mexico", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graffiti"}
{"title_page": "Thierry Mukuta", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{orphan|date=March 2017}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2017}}\n}}\n{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Thierry Mukuta Kiesse\n| image = Thierry mukuta.jpg\n| caption = Thierry Mukuta Kiesse in Algeria\n| fullname =   Thierry Mukuta Kiesse\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|1|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| height = {{convert|1.87|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Defensive Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[FK Ferizaj]]\n| clubnumber =  \n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132009      \n| youthclubs1 = SCO Angers B\n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 \n| clubs1 = [[Spandauer SV]] \n| caps1 =34  \n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2010\u20132011 \n| clubs2 = [[SV Wacker Burghausen]]    \n| caps2 = 17 \n| goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2011\u20132013 \n| clubs3 = [[US Orl\u00e9ans]]                             \n| caps3 = 49 \n| goals3 = 8\n| years4 = 2014\u20132015    \n| clubs4 = [[RC Arbaa]]  \n| caps4 =  24 \n| goals4 = 4\n| years5 = 2018\u2013    \n| clubs5 = [[FK Valmiera]]  \n| caps5 =  - \n| goals5 = -\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalteam1  = DR Congo U-21\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalyears2= 2015\n| nationalteam2 = [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 3\n}}\n\n'''Thierry Mukuta Kiesse''' (born 5 January 1989 in Paris) is a French [[footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Defensive Midfielder|defensive midfielder]] in [[FK Valmiera]].\n\n==Club career==\nMukuta Kiesse started his playing career in 2005 with French club [[Angers SCO|SCO Angers B]] where he became a reference.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/archive/recup:%252Fregion%252Fla-major-league-soccer-ou-evolue-thierry-henry-recrute-ia36b49168n1714825|title=La Major League Soccer, o\u00f9 \u00e9volue Thierry Henry, recrute des joueurs fran\u00e7ais au Touquet - La Voix du Nord|website=www.lavoixdunord.fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topmercato.com/mobile/article.php?idarticle=75261&mobile=iphone|title=La MLS recrute en France !|website=www.topmercato.com}}</ref> In 2009, he moved to German division [[Spandauer SV]] club in the [[Regionalliga Berlin (1963\u201374)|Regionalliga Berlin 1]] where he played 36 games and scoring 6 goals. The defensive midfielder was recruited in [[3. Liga|3.Liga]] [[SV Wacker Burghausen]] club, in 2010, where he was trained by the famous [[Mario Basler]]. In 2011, Mukuta Kiesse decided to return in France to join the [[Ligue 2]] [[US Orl\u00e9ans]] club for a season where he appeared in 49 of their matches and scoring 8 goals. Mukuta Kiesse joined the [[Ligue 1]] Algerian [[RC Arbaa]] club in 2014.\n\n==International career==\nThierry Mukuta made three appearances for the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] under-21 and was also invited to the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo national football team|senior national team]] in 2015 by coach [[Florent Ibeng\u00e9]] where he also made three appearances for the national team.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{soccerway}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mukuta, Thierry}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo international footballers]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo footballers]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Valmieras FK players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{orphan|date=March 2017}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2017}}\n}}\n{{short description|French footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Thierry Mukuta Kiesse\n| image = Thierry mukuta.jpg\n| caption = Thierry Mukuta Kiesse in Algeria\n| fullname =   Thierry Mukuta Kiesse\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|1|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| height = {{convert|1.87|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Defensive Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[FK Ferizaj]]\n| clubnumber =  \n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132009      \n| youthclubs1 = SCO Angers B\n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 \n| clubs1 = [[Spandauer SV]] \n| caps1 =34  \n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2010\u20132011 \n| clubs2 = [[SV Wacker Burghausen]]    \n| caps2 = 17 \n| goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2011\u20132013 \n| clubs3 = [[US Orl\u00e9ans]]                             \n| caps3 = 49 \n| goals3 = 8\n| years4 = 2014\u20132015    \n| clubs4 = [[RC Arbaa]]  \n| caps4 =  24 \n| goals4 = 4\n| years5 = 2018\u2013    \n| clubs5 = [[FK Valmiera]]  \n| caps5 =  - \n| goals5 = -\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalteam1  = DR Congo U-21\n| nationalcaps1  = 3\n| nationalyears2= 2015\n| nationalteam2 = [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 3\n}}\n\n'''Thierry Mukuta Kiesse''' (born 5 January 1989 in Paris) is a French [[footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Defensive Midfielder|defensive midfielder]] in [[FK Valmiera]].\n\n==Club career==\nMukuta Kiesse started his playing career in 2005 with French club [[Angers SCO|SCO Angers B]] where he became a reference.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/archive/recup:%252Fregion%252Fla-major-league-soccer-ou-evolue-thierry-henry-recrute-ia36b49168n1714825|title=La Major League Soccer, o\u00f9 \u00e9volue Thierry Henry, recrute des joueurs fran\u00e7ais au Touquet - La Voix du Nord|website=www.lavoixdunord.fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topmercato.com/mobile/article.php?idarticle=75261&mobile=iphone|title=La MLS recrute en France !|website=www.topmercato.com}}</ref> In 2009, he moved to German division [[Spandauer SV]] club in the [[Regionalliga Berlin (1963\u201374)|Regionalliga Berlin 1]] where he played 36 games and scoring 6 goals. The defensive midfielder was recruited in [[3. Liga|3.Liga]] [[SV Wacker Burghausen]] club, in 2010, where he was trained by the famous [[Mario Basler]]. In 2011, Mukuta Kiesse decided to return in France to join the [[Ligue 2]] [[US Orl\u00e9ans]] club for a season where he appeared in 49 of their matches and scoring 8 goals. Mukuta Kiesse joined the [[Ligue 1]] Algerian [[RC Arbaa]] club in 2014.\n\n==International career==\nThierry Mukuta made three appearances for the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] under-21 and was also invited to the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo national football team|senior national team]] in 2015 by coach [[Florent Ibeng\u00e9]] where he also made three appearances for the national team.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* [http://www.scoresway.com/?sport=soccer&page=player&id=546111 Scoresway.com Profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mukuta, Thierry}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo international footballers]]\n[[Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo footballers]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Valmieras FK players]]\n", "name_user": "Pelmeen10", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal Links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thierry_Mukuta"}
{"title_page": "Luis Abreg\u00fa", "text_new": "{{short description|Argentine boxer}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n| name        = Luis Carlos Abregu\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = \n| realname    = Luis Carlos Abregu\n| nickname    = El Potro\n| weight      = [[Welterweight]]\n| height      = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}\n| reach       = \n| nationality = {{flagicon|Argentina}} [[Argentine]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1982|12|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Chicligasta Department|Chicligasta]], [[Tucuman]], Argentina\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| style       = Orthodox\n| total       = 39\n| wins        = 36\n| losses      = 3\n| draws       = 0\n| no contests = 0\n| KO          = 29\n}}\n\n'''Luis Carlos Abregu''' (born 15 December 1982) is an Argentine  professional [[Boxing|boxer]] who currently competes in the [[welterweight]] division.\n\n==Professional career==\nAbregu made his professional debut on March 4, 2005 against fellow Argentine Alberto Evaristo Torres. Abregu won the fight by [[Knockout|technical knockout]] in the third round, giving him his first professional win. Abregu built up a record of 19-0, all fought in his native Argentina, before fighting overseas for the first time as he travelled to the [[United States]] to beat Christian Solano.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=170917&cat=boxer |title=boxer: Luis Carlos Abregu| publisher= Boxrec|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nHis first loss came at the hands of [[Timothy Bradley]]. Bradley, who moved up from [[light welterweight]], won the match on a unanimous decision on July 17, 2010 at the [[Agua Caliente Casino Resort Spa|Agua Caliente Casino]] in [[Rancho Mirage]], [[California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=5208294 |title=Fight set for Bradley, Abregu| publisher= ESPN|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"tex