   = 39\n| wins        = 36\n| losses      = 3\n| draws       = 0\n| no contests = 0\n| KO          = 29\n}}\n\n'''Luis Carlos Abregu''' (born 15 December 1982) is an Argentine  professional [[Boxing|boxer]] who currently competes in the [[welterweight]] division.\n\n==Professional career==\nAbregu made his professional debut on March 4, 2005 against fellow Argentine Alberto Evaristo Torres. Abregu won the fight by [[Knockout|technical knockout]] in the third round, giving him his first professional win. Abregu built up a record of 19-0, all fought in his native Argentina, before fighting overseas for the first time as he travelled to the [[United States]] to beat Christian Solano.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=170917&cat=boxer |title=boxer: Luis Carlos Abregu| publisher= Boxrec|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nHis first loss came at the hands of [[Timothy Bradley]]. Bradley, who moved up from [[light welterweight]], won the match on a unanimous decision on July 17, 2010 at the [[Agua Caliente Casino]] in [[Rancho Mirage]], [[California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/sports/boxing/news/story?id=5208294 |title=Fight set for Bradley, Abregu| publisher= ESPN|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=8|'''36 Wins''' (29 knockouts), '''3 Losses''' (2 knockout)<ref>{{cite web | url =http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=170917&cat=boxer | title =Luis Abregu Professional boxing record | publisher =BoxRec.com}}</ref>\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#e3e3e3;\"\n!Res.\n!Record\n!Opponent\n!Type\n!Round<br>Time\n!Date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|- \n|{{no2}}Loss||36\u20133||align=left|{{flagicon|ARG}} Juan Carlos Pedrozo\n|{{small|TKO}}\n|{{small|3 (8)}}\n|{{small|2016-09-23}}\n|align=left|{{small|{{flagicon|ARG}} Complejo Deportivo Nicol\u00e1s Vitale, Salta, Salta, Argentina}}\n|align=l