{"title_page": "In Store Jam", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = In Store Jam\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = Jamiroquai\n| cover      = In store jam.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1997 <small>([[United States|US]])</small>\n| recorded   = 1993-1996\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Funk]], [[acid jazz]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[Soul music|soul]], [[Pop music|pop]], [[disco]]\n| length     = 42:34\n| label      = [[Sony Music]]\n| producer   = Pete Spence\n| prev_title = [[Travelling Without Moving]]\n| prev_year  = 1996\n| next_title = [[Synkronized]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\n'''In Store Jam''' is the second compilation album released by [[United Kingdom|British]] [[funk]]/[[acid jazz]] band [[Jamiroquai]]. Released as a promotional album in 1997, the record features a selection of tracks from all three of the group's early studio albums, as well as an additional live recording of [[Kool & the Gang]]'s \"[[Hollywood Swinging]]\". All of the tracks from the album have, or been considered to become, singles. The album was only released in the [[United States]].<ref>http://eil.com/shop/moreinfo.asp?catalogid=97305</ref> Two versions of the release were available: a standard [[CD]], and a [[cassette tape]] release, retitled '''Sampler''', with the addition of an extra track.<ref>http://funkin.com/music/singles/in_store_jam/</ref>\n\n==Track listing<ref>http://funkin.com/music/singles/in_store_jam/</ref>==\n{{Track listing\n| total_length    = 42:34\n| title1          = Everyday\n| writer1         = [[Jay Kay]], [[Toby Smith]], [[Stuart Zender]]\n| note1           = from [[Travelling Without Moving]], 1996 - Cassette Tape Only\n| length1         = 4:28\n\n| title2          = [[Virtual Insanity]]\n| writer2         = Jay Kay, Toby Smith\n| note2           = from [[Travelling Without Moving]], 1996\n| length2         = 5:40\n\n| title3      